George Lyle wrote-
Date: Sunday, October 14, 2001 10:48 PM
Subject: Re: FW: [T2] locks

>IN the lock cylinders you will find a series of thin brass plates that
>control the lock.  The key repositions the plates to unlock the door.  You
>can change the order of the plates to match your ignition key.

Those plates are called "wafers".
As previously mentioned, insert any key and file them flat.
Leave a few out if you like.
If you feel the urge to examine them, do not work on a table
with carpet on the floor, the springs will be history.
